    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen using `gqq` to format a line containing long Chinese text with punctuation marks (like `，`, `。`, `；`), the line does not break at the appropriate punctuation positions.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1.  Start `nvim` with a minimal setup (e.g., `nvim -u NONE test.txt`).\n2.  Enter the following settings and sample text:\n    ```vim\n    :set nowrap\n    ```\n   ```text\n   这是一段非常长的中文句子，它包含了很多逗号和句号；但是当使用gqq进行格式化时，换行并没有在标点符号处正确发生，导致格式看起来很混乱。\n   ```\n3. Move the cursor to that line\n4. run `gqq`.\n\n<img width=\"1866\" height=\"127\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e63dd447-1ff3-4bc2-b417-72571bf16bb5\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe formatter should recognize Chinese punctuation marks (e.g., `，`, `。`, `；`, `！`, `？`) as valid line break positions and prefer breaking lines at these locations.\n\n<img width=\"1866\" height=\"159\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/118a3eac-9247-49c0-b963-dc6bd371b636\" />\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.4\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, 9.1.2025\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nGentoo Linux x86_64\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nghostty 1.1.3\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo, system package manager(both)",
